The Programming language L - Lexical Definition
______________________________________________


15 Reserved words
begin    do     else     end      fi
if       int    od       print    prog
read     real   then     var     while   


6 Reserved symbols
(   )   , 
:   ;   .             (Note: last sign is an endpoint


5 Composed tokens
id:             letter (letter|digit)*
num:            digit+  |       digit+.digit*
relop:          =       |       <>      |       <       |       >
matop:          +       |       -       |       *       |       /
assign:         :=              



  Where:  (Note: digit and letter are not tokens)
   digit:  0  |  1  | ... |  9
   letter: a  |  b  | ... |  z  |  A  |  B  | ... | Z


